name: DimensionSettingsTest
description: To see the effects of this test mod you must create a new world then teleport to the custom dimension (use: /execute in dimension_settings_test:test_overworld run tp @s ...). You should observe that the only structure that generates in the dimension is the ruined portal and it should do so very frequently. Note: This mod adds a data asset located at: /data/dimension_settings_test/dimension/test_overworld.json

methods.name: registerSettings
methods.description: Demonstrates how a mod can register custom DimensionSettings which can be referenced from within a datapack dimension config whilst being discoverable for other mods to add to and remove structures etc from.

methods.name: addStructure
methods.description: Demonstrates how a mod could handle adding their structure settings to a specific dimension.

methods.name: createDimensionSettings
methods.description: Create a DimensionSettings instance copying all but the structure settings from overworld.
